-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2014 06:01AM EDT
-- None



May 14 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Wednesday:

** Yahoo Inc <YHOO.O> has bought Blink, a mobile messaging startup that lets users send messages that self-destruct at a time set by the sender. [ID:nL3N0O03N6]  ** Austrian crane maker Palfinger <PALF.VI> has sold new shares to China's Sany Heavy Industry Co Ltd <600031.SS> in a deal to consolidate their strategic partnership, it said on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0O020U]  ** BHP Billiton <BHP.AX> is in talks to sell its Australian nickel business, the top global miner said on Wednesday, in line with its aim of simplifying the company. [ID:nL3N0O01OB]  ** China's state-backed Citic Pacific Ltd <0267.HK> said on Wednesday that an independent financial advisor had found the terms and conditions of its proposed acquisition of some of its parent's assets fair. [ID:nL3N0O03ND]  ** The euro zone's biggest bank, Santander <SAN.MC>, is close to selling a stake in its securities custody business, worth up to 1 billion euros ($1.38 billion) as a whole, to several private equity firms, Expansion newspaper reported on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0O021Z]  ** Pfizer <PFE.N> faces calls to extend its commitment to UK jobs and research to least 10 years, as the U.S. drug maker's boss prepares for a second day of questioning from lawmakers over its plan to buy AstraZeneca <AZN.L>. [ID:nL6N0NZ68Q]  ** A consortium that includes Singapore tycoon Ong Beng Seng and Wheelock Properties (Singapore) Ltd <WPSL.SI> has increased its offer price for a stake in Hotel Properties Ltd to S$4 per share, valuing the company at around S$2.07 billion ($1.65 billion). [ID:nL3N0O00GZ]  ** Etisalat <ETEL.AD> has completed its purchase of a 53-percent stake in Maroc Telecom from Paris-listed Vivendi <VIV.PA> for 4.14 billion euros, the United Arab Emirates operator said in a statement on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0O02L0]  ($1 = 0.7270 Euros)